# Testing policy

Non-UI logic changes require tests. Run `make check` before finishing.

| Layer | Required? | Approach |
|-------|-----------|----------|
| `io/` | Yes | Check unit tests |
| `layout/` | Yes | Check unit tests |
| `nav/` | Yes | Check unit tests |
| `cmd/` | Yes | Check unit tests |
| `app/` | Yes for wiring | Integration-style (`viewer-tests.c`) |
| `ui/` | No direct tests | Extract testable logic to lower layers |

## Conventions

- Test file mirrors module: `csv-reader.c` → `csv-parser-tests.c`, `navigation.c` → `navigation-tests.c`.
- Shared fixtures: `tests/mock-token.*`, `tests/test-resources.*`.
- Register new tests in `tests/Makefile.am` (`check_PROGRAMS` and `TESTS`).

```bash
make check                    # full suite
./configure --enable-coverage && make check   # with coverage
```

Do not merge non-UI logic changes without corresponding tests.
